Description: Body and handle sherd of East Greek pottery cup; small horizontal handle attached to wall; buff clay with pale grey-brown surface, not readily distinguished from dull brown glaze. Interior; rim glazed, four lines between bands preserved on lower wall; exterior: lip reserved with band at bottom; rest of wall perhaps wholly glazed, save between handle roots.
Curator's comments: A piece that does not chime in with regular cup production.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.229)
